Amad Diallo has paid tribute to Rangers’ fans after leaving the club following his loan from Manchester United. The 19-year-old joined the Ibrox club in the January transfer window. He scored three goals for Giovanni van Bronckhorst’s men, but failed to live up to the hype that surrounded him upon joining. -Advertisement- However, he heads back to Old Trafford with a Scottish Cup winners medal. And one week on, the Ivorian has thanked the club and its fans looking after him during his spell in Glasgow. Diallo wrote on Twitter: “Thanks guys it was a pleasure to be part of your beautiful trip…wish you all the best.” Accompanying his kind words, he shared video compilation of his best bits while at Rangers. This included a goal on his debut away to Ross County after just four-minutes.